XP may refer to:

Computing
* Windows XP, a discontinued operating system
* Athlon XP, a series of AMD microprocessors
* Extreme programming, a software development methodology 
* XP, a complexity class in parameterized complexity

Other
* Chi Rho, a Christian symbol
* Experience point, a unit of measurement in role-playing games
* Xeroderma pigmentosum, a genetic disorder
* Xtra Airways, by IATA code
* XP, in the list of emoticons
* Experimental pursuit, by USAAC aircraft designation, such as the Lockheed XP-38 Lightning
* Ilford XP2 Super, a chromogenic black and white film made by Ilford Photo
* Experimental test pilot

